
[1]derision

   DERISION, n.

   1. The act of laughing at in contempt.

   2. Contempt manifested by laughter; scorn.

   I am in derision daily. Jer. 20.

   3. An object of derision or contempt; a laughing-stock.

   I was a derision to all my people. Lam 3.
